$interpreted: Miranda: (Damn, it's been days and I still haven't seen her...)

Wolf Contestant: Hey! I heard you've been harassing Himawari!
Guess it's no surprise the student of that nutjob turns out to be a nutjob herself.
Miranda: Me? Weren't you the one pretty much begging Master Law to take you in? What, are you jealous now?
Wolf Contestant: Jealous!? Don't flatter yourself.
Yellow-Team Leader: Hello contestants! It's time for your first challenge!
Bull Contestant: Now!? Half the contestants haven't even arrived yet!
Miranda: Unless the other team's challenge is starting somewhere else?
Alliance Soldier: That's right! Tournament preliminaries are taking place in one of the Water Sect's ruined cities, which is about a days trip from here.
Alliance Soldier: Your first challenge is to make it there by the end of the day tomorrow. If you don't, you'll be disqualified from continuing in the tournament!
Seahorse Contestant: That's it?
Seahorse Contestant: Just get to the city?
Alliance Soldier: That's right. But you'll have to be careful, as the city is surrounded by all types of dangerous monsters. Don't let your guard down!
Turtle Contestant: So the other team's challenge is the same as ours?
Alliance Soldier: Yes, but they're starting from the other direction.
Alliance Soldier: And there's the starting beacon! Your challenge has begun!
Miranda: Listen, we're cut from the same cloth. We're both Wolf-Tribe apprentices, so why are you always singling me out?
Wolf Contestant: We are not! Just because your loony old teacher admits human students doesn't give you the right to act like we're the same.
Wolf Contestant: You know there can only be one winner in this tournament. Gonna have to get rid of each other sooner or later.
Miranda: You're not wrong there.
Wolf Contestant: What the!?
Miranda: Thanks for the tip. I'll be taking the lead, now.
Turtle Contestant: Hey! Don't come any closer!
Seahorse Contestant: Just run away!
Miranda: (Ugh... I can't just leave them, can I?)
Miranda: Make way!
Miranda: You gonna help me out, or what!?
Bull Contestant: Is it... dead?
Miranda: Yeesh! What a pain...
Miranda: Is everyone okay?
Turtle Contestant: Yeah...
Wolf Contestant: Still needed our help just to kill a measly little beast, huh? What's all that strength of yours good for, anyway?
Miranda: ...Excuse me?
Wolf Contestant: Guess all those muscles are just for show, huh? When push comes to shove, you've got nothing. You're useless!
Wolf Contestant: Look at that reaction. I hit a nerve, didn't I?
Miranda: Three, two, one! That's right, just try to get back up!
Miranda: You have no right to talk to me like that!
Bull Contestant: I don't think we should be sleeping, it's a waste of time.
Seahorse Contestant: Well, once we get there tomorrow we'll be fighting the other team. It won't help if we're tired.
Turtle Contestant: Would you both shut it!? Just cause' yer not tired doesn't mean I ain't.
Miranda: (Why do I feel like we're not the only ones here?)
Miranda: (I should check the perimeter...)
Wolf Contestant: (I don't think anyone's looking... I'll just slip this in here...)
Miranda: (Hmph... Guess it was nobody. Didn't even see any beasts. I must be tired... should get back to sleep...)
Wolf Contestant: (...If I've got anyone to blame it's that idiot Law for taking you in.)
Seahorse Contestant: A-A-Aren't these the beasts from yesterday!?
Bull Contestant: You think they're here for revenge!?
Turtle Contestant: They're surroundin' us! ...We're not gonna die here, are we!?
Miranda: Hey, get your head in the game!
Wolf Contestant: Miranda's right!
Miranda: So I'm right, for once?
Wolf Contestant: Maybe we should split up, lure them out in different directions and deal with 'em seperately.
Miranda: Seems like we're on the same page! Let's do it!
Miranda: Huh? Why're they all chasing me!?
Bull Contestant: Oh no, they knocked her off the cliff! Let's go help her!
Wolf Contestant: You idiot! This is our chance to get away! We've got the glory of our tribes on our shoulders! Who cares about her?
Bull Contestant: But... But she saved us yesterday...
Wolf Contestant: What's more important? Her, or our friendship?
Wolf Contestant: If you screw up your shot at the tournament just to save a human, you'll be the shame of your whole tribe.
Wolf Contestant: Think about it!
Seahorse Contestant: The... The mountain's collapsing! Run!
Turtle Contestant: Yaaaaaaagh!!!
Miranda: Ow... that was a bad fall...
Miranda: ...Damn, I haven't fulfilled my promise, yet. I can't die here...
Miranda: This is... one of those beasts' teeth? Is it from yesterday? Why would it be in my bag?
Miranda: Were they attracted to its scent?
Miranda: Damnit! They set me up!
Miranda: (Alright, while they've still got their backs to me...!)

Miranda: (Whew... Got 'em...
Now, I need to get to the tournament grounds...)
Miranda: ...Himawari... I'm sorry... I tried my best...
